      "title": "Location (Where?) - Locative Case",
      "titleLT": "Vietininko linksnis",
      "explanation": "To express location (where something is), use the locative case with prepositions like 'pas' (at someone's place) or just the locative ending. Common endings: -e, -je, -yje.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "lithuanian": "Aš esu mokykloje.",
